[
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪ Bass music playing ♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=2"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=5"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=7"
  },
  {
    "text": "Marin Eubanks: Hi, everyone.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "I’m Marin, an engineer on the ClassKit team, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=10"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I’m excited to show you a new API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=12"
  },
  {
    "text": "we’ve added to ClassKit for file-based apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=14"
  },
  {
    "text": "Today, I’ll go over Schoolwork and how it’s used with ClassKit.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=17"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, I’ll do an in-depth review of the new API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=21"
  },
  {
    "text": "for file-based apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, I’ll walk you through a sample implementation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=27"
  },
  {
    "text": "And finally, I’ll show you how to test the new API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=31"
  },
  {
    "text": "using ClassKit’s developer mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=34"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let me start by giving you a brief overview of Schoolwork.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=37"
  },
  {
    "text": "Schoolwork is an educational app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "that enables teachers to share assignments ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=44"
  },
  {
    "text": "in which students use your apps to learn.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=47"
  },
  {
    "text": "When your app adopts the ClassKit framework ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=50"
  },
  {
    "text": "and advertises assignable content -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=52"
  },
  {
    "text": "known as CLSContexts -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=54"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as starts reporting progress data on activities, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "teachers will be able to assign that content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=59"
  },
  {
    "text": "and view the progress data reported by your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=62"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app is ClassKit-enabled, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "teachers will be more likely to use your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=67"
  },
  {
    "text": "in their curriculum.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=70"
  },
  {
    "text": "And coming soon, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "Schoolwork will be even easier to use ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=72"
  },
  {
    "text": "and adds many new features to streamline teacher workflows, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=74"
  },
  {
    "text": "inform instruction, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "and provide data from your apps to teachers.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=80"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that we’re familiar with Schoolwork, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=83"
  },
  {
    "text": "let’s see how the data from your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=85"
  },
  {
    "text": "flows into Schoolwork.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=87"
  },
  {
    "text": "Your app submits data to the ClassKit framework.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=90"
  },
  {
    "text": "ClassKit surfaces that data to the Schoolwork app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "The data is then presented to the student and teacher.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is a view of Schoolwork ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=101"
  },
  {
    "text": "with a few assignments of ClassKit-enabled apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=102"
  },
  {
    "text": "If we tap on one of the assignments, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=105"
  },
  {
    "text": "we can see an example of an app which has adopted ClassKit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=108"
  },
  {
    "text": "and reported student-progress data.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=113"
  },
  {
    "text": "We will go through the details of this use case a bit later.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=115"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that we have reviewed Schoolwork, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "let’s talk about our new file-based progress API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=122"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are more than 190,000 education apps ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=126"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the App Store.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "And while a lot of you have adopted ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=131"
  },
  {
    "text": "ClassKit’s context-based APIs, not all of you have.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=132"
  },
  {
    "text": "We received feedback ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=137"
  },
  {
    "text": "specifically around apps that interact with files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how you wanted to adopt ClassKit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=141"
  },
  {
    "text": "but contexts didn’t quite fit your use case.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=144"
  },
  {
    "text": "Well, if you’ve been holding out on ClassKit adoption ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=147"
  },
  {
    "text": "because your app is file-based, we added a new API just for you.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "This new API is for any app that interacts with files.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=156"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you have an app that can edit files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=161"
  },
  {
    "text": "or just open and view a file, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=163"
  },
  {
    "text": "then you’ll love our new API for file-based apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=165"
  },
  {
    "text": "Adopting this new API enables reporting student progress data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=168"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the files used within your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=172"
  },
  {
    "text": "when they are assigned in Schoolwork.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=175"
  },
  {
    "text": "When a teacher assigns content from a ClassKit-enabled app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=177"
  },
  {
    "text": "they will be provided additional insights, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=180"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is a win for them ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=182"
  },
  {
    "text": "and a great new use case for your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=184"
  },
  {
    "text": "One important thing to note ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=186"
  },
  {
    "text": "is that your app must adopt Open in Place.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "When your app supports Open in Place, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=191"
  },
  {
    "text": "the exact file shared between the student and teacher ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=193"
  },
  {
    "text": "will open in your app and not a copy.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=196"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's the new API for adding progress data to a file.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=198"
  },
  {
    "text": "It’s called fetchActivity, and it lives on CLSDataStore.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=202"
  },
  {
    "text": "I have both the async and async alternative versions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "of this API shown here.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=209"
  },
  {
    "text": "You’ll pass in the file URL of your file to this API, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=211"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it returns a CLSActivity.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=215"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once you have the CLSActivity, you can add progress data to it.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=217"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, let’s take a look at the types of progress data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=221"
  },
  {
    "text": "your app can submit.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=224"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you’ve already adopted ClassKit, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=225"
  },
  {
    "text": "then this will be a review ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=228"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the current progress data types we have available.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you’re new to ClassKit, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=232"
  },
  {
    "text": "these classes are currently being used on CLSContexts, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "but the same data types can also be applied to files.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=237"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here we have a CLSActivity.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=241"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is a class used to encapsulate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=244"
  },
  {
    "text": "all of the progress data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=246"
  },
  {
    "text": "associated with a particular file.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=247"
  },
  {
    "text": "We have a few types of data that can be added to a CLSActivity.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=249"
  },
  {
    "text": "First we have duration.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=254"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is the amount of time ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "a student spent working the assigned file.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=257"
  },
  {
    "text": "Time should be reported on all file types.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=260"
  },
  {
    "text": "To use this API, you simply call the start and stop methods ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=263"
  },
  {
    "text": "that live on CLSActivity.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=267"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next we have progress.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=270"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is some value between zero and one.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=272"
  },
  {
    "text": "Progress is typically used when you can determine ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=275"
  },
  {
    "text": "a student's progression through a file.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=277"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, let’s say you have an audio or a video file, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=280"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the student got 50 percent of the way through.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "You would report the playback progress as .5.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "To add progress, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=290"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can either set the progress property directly ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=291"
  },
  {
    "text": "or add a range from some start to an end.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=294"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can add overlapping ranges ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=297"
  },
  {
    "text": "or the same range multiple times.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=299"
  },
  {
    "text": "We’ll handle the logic to make sure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=302"
  },
  {
    "text": "the correct progress is reported to students and teachers.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=303"
  },
  {
    "text": "We also have the primaryActivityItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=308"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is useful if you have a file that can be edited.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=311"
  },
  {
    "text": "Setting the primaryActivityItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=315"
  },
  {
    "text": "indicates that, this piece of data, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=316"
  },
  {
    "text": "you want to highlight to students and teachers, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=318"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it shows up in the main part of the UI in the Schoolwork app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=321"
  },
  {
    "text": "There's also ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=324"
  },
  {
    "text": "an additionalActivityItems property.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is an array of CLSActivityItems ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=328"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is useful for adding additional metadata.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=331"
  },
  {
    "text": "To add a primaryActivityItem, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=334"
  },
  {
    "text": "set the primaryActivityItem property on CLSActivity.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=337"
  },
  {
    "text": "To add an additionalActivityItem, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=341"
  },
  {
    "text": "call the addAdditionalActivityItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=343"
  },
  {
    "text": "function on CLSActivity ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=346"
  },
  {
    "text": "and pass in the activityItem you want to add.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=348"
  },
  {
    "text": "The primaryActivityItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=353"
  },
  {
    "text": "and additionalActivityItem properties hold a reference ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=354"
  },
  {
    "text": "to one of our three subclasses of CLSActivityItem.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=358"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can add any of the following subclasses: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=362"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, we have CLSBinaryItem.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=365"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is used to represent any binary data type.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=368"
  },
  {
    "text": "An example usage of this might be a question on a quiz.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=371"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's say the student got it correct or incorrect.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=375"
  },
  {
    "text": "Or you can add CLSQuantityItem.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=378"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is used for any generic numerical value.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=381"
  },
  {
    "text": "You could use this for the number of pages, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=384"
  },
  {
    "text": "number of slides, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=386"
  },
  {
    "text": "or total word count on a document.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=388"
  },
  {
    "text": "And the last is CLSScoreItem.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=391"
  },
  {
    "text": "This class is used for anything that be represented ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=393"
  },
  {
    "text": "as a part out of a total.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=396"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, a score on a quiz; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=398"
  },
  {
    "text": "the user got eight out of ten.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=400"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can add any combination of these subclasses ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=403"
  },
  {
    "text": "to an activity, one of them, or all of them.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=406"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that we know the types of data that we can add, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=411"
  },
  {
    "text": "let’s walk through a code sample ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=414"
  },
  {
    "text": "of adopting this API into an app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=416"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here I have a sample app that can open and edit a text file.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=420"
  },
  {
    "text": "When the student opens the text file, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=424"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll start the timer.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=426"
  },
  {
    "text": "The student will go through, edit the file.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "When the student is about to close the file, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=431"
  },
  {
    "text": "I’ll record the total word count and stop the timer.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=433"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let’s navigate to the part of my code ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=437"
  },
  {
    "text": "that gets called when I open the file ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=439"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the student starts interacting with it.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=442"
  },
  {
    "text": "I have an openFile function.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=445"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is where I will start tracking time.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=447"
  },
  {
    "text": "In your app, you’ll go to the part of the code ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=449"
  },
  {
    "text": "that you already have for opening a file, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=452"
  },
  {
    "text": "and this is where you’ll add a little bit of code ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=455"
  },
  {
    "text": "to start the timer.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=457"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, I’ll fetch the CLS activity ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=460"
  },
  {
    "text": "for my file URL.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=462"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once I have the activity, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=465"
  },
  {
    "text": "I will call start to start tracking time ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=466"
  },
  {
    "text": "and then I will call save on CLSDataStore ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=469"
  },
  {
    "text": "to commit the changes I’ve made.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=472"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let’s go ahead and add a breakpoint here ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=475"
  },
  {
    "text": "that we’ll come back to later when testing our implementation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=477"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, I also want to stop the timer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=481"
  },
  {
    "text": "when the student is done and add a primaryActivityItem.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=483"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let’s navigate to the part of my code that gets called ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=486"
  },
  {
    "text": "when the student is about to close the file.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=489"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here I’ll call ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=491"
  },
  {
    "text": "CLSDataStore.shared. fetchActivity, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=492"
  },
  {
    "text": "grab the primaryActivityItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=496"
  },
  {
    "text": "to update it if it already exists, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=498"
  },
  {
    "text": "or create a new CLSQuantityItem if there wasn’t already one.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=501"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once I have the CLSQuantityItem, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=505"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can update its value and set it ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=507"
  },
  {
    "text": "as the primaryActivityItem on my activity.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=509"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can add progress to my activity.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=513"
  },
  {
    "text": "And last, call stop to stop the timer.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=515"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, I make sure to call save.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=518"
  },
  {
    "text": "If we don’t call save on CLSDataStore, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=521"
  },
  {
    "text": "then we will not persist any of the changes we just made.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=524"
  },
  {
    "text": "I’m going to add a breakpoint here as well.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=528"
  },
  {
    "text": "We’ll use this to help us debug our submission ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=530"
  },
  {
    "text": "of student progress data.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=533"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that we’ve adopted the API into our sample app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=535"
  },
  {
    "text": "let’s see how we can test our implementation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=539"
  },
  {
    "text": "using Schoolwork and developer mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=542"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, we need to set the ClassKit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=545"
  },
  {
    "text": "environment entitlement to development.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=547"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is inside of Xcode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=550"
  },
  {
    "text": "The default value is production.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=553"
  },
  {
    "text": "We’ll change the value of the entitlement ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=555"
  },
  {
    "text": "to development so that we can test ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=557"
  },
  {
    "text": "using developer mode and Schoolwork.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=559"
  },
  {
    "text": "The next time we run our code, it will run in developer mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=562"
  },
  {
    "text": "It’s important to make sure to set this back to production ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=566"
  },
  {
    "text": "after you're done testing.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=569"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, we need to turn on developer mode on our iPad.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=572"
  },
  {
    "text": "We'll open the Settings app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=576"
  },
  {
    "text": "navigate to Developer > ClassKit API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=578"
  },
  {
    "text": "We’ll select Teacher ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=582"
  },
  {
    "text": "to change our role to a teacher in Schoolwork.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=584"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, we will we open the Schoolwork app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=587"
  },
  {
    "text": "When Schoolwork opens, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=590"
  },
  {
    "text": "we are presented with the teacher UI.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=591"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if we tap on the Create Assignment button ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=594"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the top right-hand corner, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=597"
  },
  {
    "text": "we can create an assignment adding a file our app supports ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=599"
  },
  {
    "text": "by tapping the Files button.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=602"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then we will select the file that we want to add, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=606"
  },
  {
    "text": "enter the class and the title of the assignment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=610"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can also optionally add any instructional text ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=613"
  },
  {
    "text": "if you’d like.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=617"
  },
  {
    "text": "And then tap the button in the top right-hand corner ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=618"
  },
  {
    "text": "to publish this assignment to the class.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=621"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that we've created the assignment, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=624"
  },
  {
    "text": "we can switch our role to act as a student ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=626"
  },
  {
    "text": "and test our implementation of submitting progress data.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=629"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let's navigate back to the Settings app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=633"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Settings, we’ll select Developer > ClassKit API, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=637"
  },
  {
    "text": "and tap on Student.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=642"
  },
  {
    "text": "This has now changed my role in Schoolwork ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=644"
  },
  {
    "text": "to act as a student.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=646"
  },
  {
    "text": "We'll go back to the Schoolwork app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=648"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can see I am now logged in as a student ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=651"
  },
  {
    "text": "because I no longer have the Create Assignment button ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=654"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the top right-hand corner of my UI.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=657"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the middle of the screen, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=660"
  },
  {
    "text": "I see the assignment we just created, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=661"
  },
  {
    "text": "and if I tap on it, I am shown the details of the assignment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=663"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can tap on the file icon, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=668"
  },
  {
    "text": "and that will deep-link me into my app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=669"
  },
  {
    "text": "where I start reporting progress data.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=672"
  },
  {
    "text": "The file opens up in my app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=675"
  },
  {
    "text": "and my code gets called to start the timer.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=677"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here we can see our breakpoint get hit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=680"
  },
  {
    "text": "after calling save to start the timer.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=682"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if we hit Play and then go back to our app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=685"
  },
  {
    "text": "I see the Student Progress banner drop down from the top, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=689"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is an indication that the save was successful ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=693"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the timer was started.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=695"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then I'll go through, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=697"
  },
  {
    "text": "add a bunch of text to complete the essay.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=698"
  },
  {
    "text": "My sample app has a Done button the student will tap ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=702"
  },
  {
    "text": "when they are done editing the file.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=705"
  },
  {
    "text": "So I’ll tap that Done button in the top left-hand corner.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=707"
  },
  {
    "text": "At this point, my closeFile function will get called.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=710"
  },
  {
    "text": "We can see our second breakpoint was hit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=715"
  },
  {
    "text": "for saving the wordCount as the primaryActivityItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=717"
  },
  {
    "text": "and stopping the timer.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=720"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, we can hit Play and go back to Schoolwork.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=721"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Schoolwork, I can see the progress data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=725"
  },
  {
    "text": "submitted by my app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=727"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, I see the time as 41 minutes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=729"
  },
  {
    "text": "This validates that I'm calling start, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=732"
  },
  {
    "text": "stop, and save correctly.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=734"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, I see the word count, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=738"
  },
  {
    "text": "which I set as the primaryActivityItem.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=739"
  },
  {
    "text": "Any CLSActivityItem subclass ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=742"
  },
  {
    "text": "I set as the primaryActivityItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=744"
  },
  {
    "text": "will show up here in the main part of the UI.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=746"
  },
  {
    "text": "The fact that I can see my word count as 558 words ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=748"
  },
  {
    "text": "validates that my submission of CLSQuantityItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=753"
  },
  {
    "text": "is working correctly.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=756"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, let’s switch our role back to a teacher ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=758"
  },
  {
    "text": "and see how the data submitted by my app appears to teachers.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=760"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the center of the screen, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=764"
  },
  {
    "text": "we see I have the average time and average word count ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=765"
  },
  {
    "text": "for all students.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=768"
  },
  {
    "text": "Below that is a row for every student on the assignment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=770"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the Student cell, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=775"
  },
  {
    "text": "I see the data that one student submitted.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=776"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if I tap on the Student cell, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=779"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can see the progress data reported by my app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=782"
  },
  {
    "text": "We have the primaryActivityItem, time, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=785"
  },
  {
    "text": "and one additionalActivityItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=789"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is listed as Readability Grade Level.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=791"
  },
  {
    "text": "And that is how you use developer mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=794"
  },
  {
    "text": "to test your ClassKit integration.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=796"
  },
  {
    "text": "Don’t forget to set the entitlement back to production.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=798"
  },
  {
    "text": "Well, great! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=802"
  },
  {
    "text": "We covered a lot today, from the new API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=803"
  },
  {
    "text": "to testing it with developer mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=805"
  },
  {
    "text": "Even if you don’t consider your app for education, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=808"
  },
  {
    "text": "there’s a good chance an educator does, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=811"
  },
  {
    "text": "and having it ClassKit-enabled means your app will be ready ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=813"
  },
  {
    "text": "for them to integrate right into their curriculum.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=816"
  },
  {
    "text": "So make sure to adopt our API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=819"
  },
  {
    "text": "And thank you.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=821"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you for the feedback reports, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=822"
  },
  {
    "text": "and please submit any other feedback that you may have.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=824"
  },
  {
    "text": "We love hearing from you.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=828"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if you are interested in learning more ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=831"
  },
  {
    "text": "about our context-based APIs, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=833"
  },
  {
    "text": "take a look at our previous sessions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=835"
  },
  {
    "text": "on \"What’s new in ClassKit\" and our talk ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=836"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Introducing ClassKit\" from 2018.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=839"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thanks, and have a great WWDC! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10257/?time=841"
  },
